'''Miguel Ángel Almirón Rejala''' (born 10 February 1994) is a Paraguayan professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] or [[Midfielder#Winger|right winger]] for [[Major League Soccer]] club [[Atlanta United FC|Atlanta United]] and the [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]].

Almirón began his career at [[Cerro Porteño]] and transferred to [[Club Atlético Lanús|Lanús]] in 2015. After winning the [[2016 Argentine Primera División]], he signed for Atlanta United for $8 million. He was named in the [[MLS Best XI]] for both of his seasons in Major League Soccer, as well as [[MLS Newcomer of the Year Award|MLS Newcomer of the Year]] for 2017. After helping Atlanta to the [[MLS Cup]] in [[MLS Cup 2018|2018]], Almirón signed for [[Premier League]] side [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] for £21 million, a club record and the highest fee for an MLS player. In January 2025, Almirón returned to Atlanta United.

Almirón made his international debut for Paraguay in 2015, and represented the country at the [[Copa América]] in [[Copa América Centenario|2016]], [[2019 Copa América|2019]], [[2021 Copa América|2021]], and [[2024 Copa América|2024]].

==Early life==
Miguel Almirón was born into an impoverished family in the [[San Pablo (Asunción)|San Pablo]] neighborhood of [[Asunción]], where his father Ruben worked 18-hour shifts as a security guard and his mother Sonia worked in a supermarket.<ref name="Guardian-Angel">{{cite news |last=Taylor |first=Louise |date=11 November 2022 |title='Angel of the North': how Almirón found form to fire Newcastle dreams |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/nov/11/angel-of-the-north-how-almiron-found-form-to-fire-newcastle-dreams |work=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=12 November 2022}}</ref><ref name="Marshall">{{cite news |last=Marshall |first=Tom |date=5 December 2018 |title=Miguel Almiron's journey to MLS Cup: from Asuncion to Atlanta United FC |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/major-league-soccer/19/blog/post/3718736/miguel-almiron-journey-to-mls-cup-from-asuncion-to-atlanta-united-fc |publisher=[[ESPN]] |accessdate=12 November 2022}}</ref> He trained with [[Club 3 de Noviembre]] from the age of seven and trialed with other teams but was considered "too frail" by his coaches to become a professional footballer.<ref name="Marshall"/> The seven members of his household slept in three bedrooms, and he had to share a bed with his mother until he was 18.<ref name=talksport/><ref name=dreamed>{{cite news |last1=Kelly |first1=Ciaran |title=Exclusive: Miguel Almiron dreamed of Newcastle United transfer |url=https://www.chroniclelive.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/newcastle-utd-transfer-miguel-almiron-15787606 |access-date=11 February 2021 |work=Chronicle Live |date=7 February 2019}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Cerro Porteño===
Rejected from [[Club Nacional]] for being too lightweight, Almirón moved to [[Cerro Porteño]]. His new club still had reservations about his physique, and he did not play regularly until he was on their under-17 side.<ref name=dreamed/>

===Lanús===
In August 2015, Almirón signed for [[Club Atlético Lanús]] in the [[Argentine Primera División]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.com.ar/news/story/_/id/2435943/lanus-acordo-la-incorporacion-del-volante-miguel-almiron |title=Lanús acordó la incorporación del volante Miguel Almirón |website=ESPN |language=es |date=31 July 2015}}</ref> Introduced slowly in his first season by Lanús manager [[Guillermo Barros Schelotto]], Almirón came to the forefront the next season in the shortened [[2016 Argentine Primera División]] under [[Jorge Almirón]]. Playing as an advanced central midfielder, Almirón was pivotal in Lanús' [[2016 Argentine Primera División]] title win, scoring key goals against local rivals [[Club Atlético Banfield|Banfield]] in the Clásico del Sur,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ole.com.ar/lanus/titulo_0_1564643549.html |title=Con personalidad |work=[[Olé (sports newspaper)|Olé]] |date=29 May 2016 |language=es |access-date=17 March 2018 |archive-date=28 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180628021236/https://www.ole.com.ar/lanus/titulo_0_1564643549.html |url-status=dead }}</ref> and later in the final against [[San Lorenzo de Almagro|San Lorenzo]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1903667-san-lorenzo-lanus-torneo-transicion |title=Campeón de punta a punta: Lanús goleó a San Lorenzo 4-0 y desató la fiesta en el Monumental |work=[[La Nación]] |date=29 May 2016 |language=es |access-date=30 September 2017 |archive-date=30 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190130110245/https://www.lanacion.com.ar/1903667-san-lorenzo-lanus-torneo-transicion |url-status=dead }}</ref> A few months later, in August 2016, Almirón set-up the only goal in Lanús' Copa Bicentenario victory over [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2016/08/14/argentina/copa-bicentenario/racing-club-de-avellaneda/ca-lanus/2324471/ |title=Racing Club vs. Lanús 0 - 1 |work=Soccerway |date=14 August 2016}}</ref>

===Atlanta United FC===

On 5 December 2016, Almirón signed with the new [[Major League Soccer]] expansion team [[Atlanta United FC]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Almiron signs with Atlanta United|url=https://twitter.com/ATLUTD/status/805851351821459456|website=Atlanta United FC (Twitter)}}</ref> He joined as a "Young Designated Player"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Volcano|first1=Carlos|title=Atlanta United sign Paraguay international Miguel Almiron - Tribal Football|url=http://www.tribalfootball.com/articles/atlanta-united-sign-paraguay-international-miguel-almiron-4158119|website=Tribal Football}}</ref> and Atlanta paid a transfer fee of around $8 million to Lanús.<ref>{{cite web|title=Atlanta United completes signing of Paraguay star Miguel Almiron|url=http://www.espnfc.com/major-league-soccer/story/3012469/miguel-almiron-move-to-atlanta-united-nearly-done-at-$8-million-sources|website=ESPN FC|date=5 December 2016}}</ref> The club also paid $50,000 in [[general allocation money]] to [[Seattle Sounders FC]], who held the MLS discovery rights to Almirón.<ref>{{cite news |last=Roberson |first=Doug |date=31 January 2025 |title=Eight years later, Atlanta United's Lagerwey and Henderson get to sign Almiron |url=https://www.ajc.com/sports/atlanta-united/eight-years-later-atlanta-uniteds-lagerwey-and-henderson-get-to-sign-almiron/5R7GLXXTE5GHXLA5233VMYL27Q/ |work=Atlanta Journal-Constitution |accessdate=31 January 2025}}</ref>

Almirón was an important figure in Atlanta United's first season, described as the "heartbeat" of the team by veteran teammate [[Jeff Larentowicz]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/09/24/atlanta-united-brace-bad-injury-news-about-heartbeat-miguel-almiron |title=Atlanta United brace for bad injury news about "heartbeat" Miguel Almiron |work=MLS Soccer |first=Payson |last=Schwin |date=24 September 2017}}</ref> On 12 March, Almirón scored his first goals for the club, notching a brace in the club's second game, a 6–1 victory over fellow MLS newcomers [[Minnesota United FC]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ajc.com/sports/atlanta-united-minnesota-united-observations/wFjrmdtScuGNirW2Kt5joK/ |title=Atlanta United 6, Minnesota United 1: 5 observations |work=Atlanta Journal-Constitution |first=Doug |last=Roberson |date=13 March 2017}}</ref> He scored the second hat-trick in club history on 20 May against the [[Houston Dynamo]], and scored two goals a week later against [[New York City FC]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/05/21/miguel-almiron-obliges-coachs-request-shoot-more-nets-hat-trick |title=Miguel Almiron obliges coach's request to shoot more, nets a hat trick |work=MLS Soccer |first=Payson |last=Schwin |date=21 May 2017}}</ref> Almirón joined teammates [[Greg Garza]] and [[Michael Parkhurst]] in the [[2017 MLS All-Star Game|MLS All-Star Game]] on 2 August,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/07/30/atlanta-united-celebrates-first-year-three-all-star-picks |title=Atlanta United celebrates first year with three All-Star picks |work=MLS Soccer |first=Payson |last=Schwin |date=30 July 2017}}</ref> and topped the league's list of 24 players under the age of 24, released on 28 September.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.atlutd.com/post/2017/09/28/miguel-almir-n-ranked-1-mls-24-under-24-list |title=Miguel Almirón ranked #1 in MLS 24 Under 24 List |work=Atlanta United |date=28 September 2017}}</ref> During the regular season, Almirón was named to seven [[2017 Major League Soccer season#Player and Team of the week|Teams of the Week]] by Major League Soccer, and was named Player of the Week twice.<ref>{{cite web |last=Boehm|first=Charles|website=[[Major League Soccer]]|date=22 May 2017|access-date=5 June 2018|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/05/22/2017-team-week-wk-12-superstars-and-men-red-shine|title=2017 Team of the Week (Wk 12): Superstars, and Men in Red, shine}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Stejskal |first1=Sam |title=Miguel Almiron wins Alcatel MLS Player of the Week for Week 12 |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/05/23/miguel-almiron-wins-alcatel-mls-player-week-week-12 |website=[[Major League Soccer]] |access-date=11 June 2018 |date=23 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Stejskal |first1=Sam |title=Miguel Almiron wins second straight Alcatel MLS Player of the Week |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/05/30/miguel-almiron-wins-second-straight-alcatel-mls-player-week |website=[[Major League Soccer]] |access-date=11 June 2018 |date=30 May 2017}}</ref> At the end of the season, he was named to the league's Best XI<ref name="mlsbestXI17">{{cite web|title=2017 MLS Best XI revealed: Who was the best in 2017?|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/11/29/2017-mls-best-xi|publisher=Major League Soccer|access-date=1 December 2017}}</ref> and was named [[MLS Newcomer of the Year Award|Newcomer of the Year]].<ref name="mlsnewcomer">{{cite web|last=Boehm|first=Charles|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/11/20/atlanta-uniteds-miguel-almiron-named-2017-mls-newcomer-year|title=Atlanta United's Miguel Almiron named 2017 MLS Newcomer of the Year|website=[[Major League Soccer]]|date=20 November 2017|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref>

In April 2018, Almirón was named MLS Player of the Month for his five goals and two assists as Atlanta went unbeaten with three wins and a draw.<ref name=potm/> With 12 goals and 14 assists, he was again named in the MLS Best XI, alongside teammate [[Josef Martínez]].<ref name=2018xi/> Atlanta won [[MLS Cup 2018]] against the [[Portland Timbers]] in only their second season of existence, and Almirón was named in the Team of the [[2018 MLS Cup Playoffs]].<ref name=MLSCupwin>{{cite news |last1=Boehm |first1=Charles |title=Team of the Audi 2018 MLS Cup Playoffs: Who made the postseason Best XI? |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2018/12/11/team-audi-2018-mls-cup-playoffs-who-made-postseason-best-xi |access-date=7 February 2019 |publisher=Major League Soccer |date=11 December 2018}}</ref>

===Newcastle United===
[[File:Miguel Almirón 2021-08-07 1.jpg|thumb|upright|Almirón playing for [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] in 2021]]

On 31 January 2019, Almirón joined [[Premier League]] side [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] for an undisclosed fee on a five-and-a-half-year deal.<ref>{{cite news |last=Easterby |first=Tom |title=Magpies complete Almirón signing |url=https://www.nufc.co.uk/news/latest-news/magpies-complete-almiron-signing |access-date=31 January 2019 |work=Newcastle United Football Club |date=31 January 2019}}</ref> The transfer fee was believed to be around £21 million, at the time a club record,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/47072107|title=Newcastle break their transfer record to sign playmaker Miguel Almiron|date=31 January 2019|website=BBC Sport|access-date=31 January 2019}}</ref> and a [[List of most expensive American soccer transfers#Highest transfer payments received by American soccer clubs|record for an MLS player]]. He made his Premier League debut on 11 February in a 1–1 draw at [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]], playing the final 18 minutes in place of [[Christian Atsu]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Waugh |first=Chris |title=Miguel Almiron debut watch: How playmaker's pace, flair and workrate whet appetite of Newcastle fans |url=https://www.chroniclelive.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/miguel-almiron-debut-wolves-newcastle-15818192 |access-date=19 February 2019 |work=Chronicle Live |date=12 February 2019}}</ref> Fans and media likened Almirón to Santiago Muñez, a fictional Newcastle player from the film [[Goal! (film)|''Goal!'']] who also originated from Latin America and moved to [[St James' Park]] via the United States.<ref>{{cite web |last=Edwards |first=Luke |title=Miguel Almiron's Newcastle move is like a film plot but he will have to write his own scripts |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2019/01/31/miguel-almirons-newcastle-move-like-movie-plot-will-have-write/ |access-date=2 March 2019 |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=31 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Musgroves |first=Andrew |title=As Newcastle fans compare Miguel Almiron to Santiago Munez - here's how the Magpies won the race to film Goal |url=https://www.chroniclelive.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/revealed-how-newcastle-united-took-13365994 |access-date=2 March 2019 |work=Chronicle Live |date=25 February 2019}}</ref><ref name=talksport>{{cite web |last=Cole |first=Jackson |title=Miguel Almiron says he dreams of 'achieving something big' with Newcastle United |url=https://talksport.com/football/490406/newcastle-miguel-almiron-dreams-achieving-something-big/ |access-date=2 March 2019 |work=Talksport |date=8 February 2019}}</ref> During a match against Southampton on 20 April, he was tackled by [[Oriol Romeu]] and suffered a hamstring injury that ruled him out for the rest of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48036979|title=Miguel Almiron: Newcastle midfielder out for season with hamstring injury|date=24 April 2019 |work=BBC Sport}}</ref> Almirón struggled to score in his first months with Newcastle, but helped his side to avoid relegation.<ref>{{cite news |last=Taylor |first=Louise |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/dec/20/miguel-almiron-desperate-first-goal-newcastle-united |title=Interview: Miguel Almirón: 'I'm desperate for the first goal. I can't wait for that moment' |work=The Guardian |date=20 December 2019 |access-date=21 December 2019}}</ref> After registering 40 shots with no goals, he scored his first Premier League goal on 21 December in a 1–0 victory over [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Mendola |first=Nicholas |date=21 December 2019 |title=Bruce raves about Almiron after Newcastle striker finally gets goal |url=https://soccer.nbcsports.com/2019/12/21/newcastle-united-premier-league-miguel-almiron-steve-bruce-andy-carroll/ |publisher=NBC Sports |access-date=21 December 2019}}</ref> He finished the season with a club-best eight goals in all competitions.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Mann |first1=Mantej |title=Newcastle United 2&ndash;2 West Ham United |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/52145656 |access-date=11 February 2021 |website=BBC Sport |date=5 July 2020}}</ref>

On 6 February 2021, Almirón scored twice in a 3–2 home win over [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]], a game in which he ran 11.29&nbsp;km, the most on his team. He then scored four goals in his last 12 Premier League games, the same as he scored in the 55 before that.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sutcliffe |first1=Steve |title=Newcastle United 3&ndash;2 Southampton |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/55867136 |access-date=11 February 2021 |website=BBC Sport |date=6 February 2021}}</ref>

On 21 August 2022, Almirón broke a goal-scoring drought by scoring an equalizer against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], following a cross from Newcastle teammate [[Allan Saint-Maximin]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62537744|title=Newcastle United 3–3 Manchester City|website=BBC Sport|first=Michael|last=Emons|date=21 August 2022|access-date=12 November 2022}}</ref> In October, Almirón scored six goals in six matches, with two goals against [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63017872|title=Fulham 1–4 Newcastle United|website=BBC Sport|first=Joe|last=Rindl|date=1 October 2022|access-date=12 November 2022}}</ref> and one each against [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63099426|title=Newcastle United 5–1 Brentford|website=BBC Sport|first=Emma|last=Smith|date=8 October 2022|access-date=12 November 2022}}</ref> [[Everton F.C.|Everton]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63224225|title=Newcastle United 1–0 Everton|website=BBC Sport|first=Alistair|last=Magowan|date=19 October 2022|access-date=12 November 2022}}</ref> [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63274136|title=Tottenham Hotspur 1–2 Newcastle United|website=BBC Sport|first=Neil|last=Johnston|date=23 October 2022|access-date=12 November 2022}}</ref> and [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]], reaching seven Premier League goals for the season, the most in his time in the [[Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63354917|title=Newcastle United 4–0 Aston Villa|website=BBC Sport|first=Matt|last=Gault|date=29 October 2022|access-date=12 November 2022}}</ref> Following that success, he won [[Premier League Player of the Month]] for [[2022–23 Premier League#Monthly awards|October 2022]] and [[Premier League Goal of the Month]] for his first-half goal against Fulham.<ref name="potm oct22">{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/2899176|title=Almiron named October EA SPORTS Player of the Month |publisher=Premier League |date=11 November 2022 |accessdate=11 November 2022}}</ref><ref name="gotm1022"/> On 6 November, Almirón continued his scoring run with the opening goal against Southampton in a 4–1 victory, scoring his seventh goal in as many games, one more than in his previous 74 Premier League appearances.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63443730|title=Southampton 1–4 Newcastle United|website=BBC Sport|first=Jonathan|last=Jurejko|date=19 October 2022|access-date=12 November 2022}}</ref> The next weekend against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], his scoring run came to an end, but he assisted [[Joe Willock]] for the only goal of the game.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63523923|title=Newcastle United 1–0 Chelsea|website=BBC Sport|first=Alistair|last=Magowan|date=12 November 2022|access-date=12 November 2022}}</ref>

[[File:Miguel Almirón Red Bull Atlanta 5.31.25-108.jpg|thumb|left|upright|Miguel Almirón with Atlanta United in 2025]]

On 24 February 2023, Almirón signed a new three-and-a-half-year contract with the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nufc.co.uk/news/latest-news/almiron-signs-new-contract-with-newcastle-united/|title=Almirón signs new contract with Newcastle United|website=Newcastle United|date=24 February 2023|accessdate=24 February 2023}}</ref> On 4 October of the same year, he scored his first goal in the [[UEFA Champions League]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tntsports.co.uk/football/champions-league/2023-2024/uefa-champions-league-newcastle-v-psg-follow-live_sto9820221/story.shtml|title=Newcastle United 4-1 PSG: Geordies thump PSG in unforgettable night at St James' Park in Champions League|website=TNT Sports|date=4 October 2023|accessdate=5 October 2023}}</ref> becoming the ninth Paraguayan player to score in the competition and putting Newcastle ahead 1–0 against [[Paris Saint-Germain]] in an eventual 4–1 win.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://d10.ultimahora.com/el-debut-en-champions-de-miguel-almiron-fue-con-empate |title=El debut de Champions de Miguel Almirón fue con empate |date=19 September 2023 |access-date=27 September 2023 |website=[[Última Hora (Paraguay)|Última Hora]] |department=D10 |language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Shread |first=Joe |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12964784/ac-milan-0-0-newcastle-eddie-howes-magpies-hold-on-for-point-against-dominant-hosts-on-champions-league-return |title=AC Milan 0-0 Newcastle: Eddie Howe's side hold on for point against dominant hosts on Champions League return |date=20 September 2023 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |access-date=27 September 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last= McNulty |first=Phil |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/67013557 |title=Newcastle United 4-1 Paris St-Germain: Magpies' win worth the 20-year wait |website=[[BBC]] |date=4 October 2023 |access-date=5 October 2023}}</ref><ref name="a">{{cite web |url=https://www.ole.com.ar/futbol-internacional/champions/almiron-newcastle-psg-gol-figura_0_R8SeDzHlD8.html |title=El ex Lanús que la rompió contra PSG y que en una semana jugará contra Argentina |date=4 October 2023 |access-date=5 October 2023 |website=Diario Olé |language=es}}</ref> His goal was Newcastle's first in the competition in over 20 years, since [[Alan Shearer]] scored in 2003.<ref name="a" /><ref>{{cite web |last=Booker |first=Adam |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/newcastle-jubilation-after-first-ucl-goal-in-20-years-against-psg-38333816 |title=Newcastle jubilation after first UCL goal in 20 years against PSG! |date=4 October 2023 |access-date=5 October 2023 |website=One Football}}</ref>
In March 2025, after Almirón had left the club, Newcastle United won the EFL Cup. As he had played four games in the cup campaign prior to leaving, Almirón received a winners medal.<ref>{{cite web |title=‘Always supporting’ - Champions League goalscorer posts Newcastle United message on eve of Barcelona clash |url=https://www.shieldsgazette.com/sport/football/newcastle-united/miguel-almiron-newcastle-united-barcelona-5322724 |website=Shields Gazette |access-date=22 September 2025}}</ref>

===Return to Atlanta United===

On 30 January 2025, Almirón rejoined Atlanta United.<ref>{{cite web |title=Welcome back, Miggy: Miguel Almirón returns to Atlanta United |url=https://www.atlutd.com/news/welcome-home-miggy-miguel-almiron-returns-to-mls-atlanta-united |website=Atlanta United Football Club |access-date=30 January 2025}}</ref> The club paid $400,000 in general allocation money to [[Charlotte FC]], who had acquired the MLS discovery rights to Almirón.<ref>{{cite news |date=January 30, 2025 |title=Charlotte FC Acquires $400,000 General Allocation Money from Atlanta United |url=https://www.charlottefootballclub.com/news/charlotte-fc-acquires-400-000-general-allocation-money-from-atlanta-united |publisher=[[Charlotte FC]] |accessdate=31 January 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Almirón played for the [[Paraguay men's national under-20 football team|Paraguay under-20 national team]] in the [[2013 South American Youth Football Championship]] in Argentina, and was highly involved as his team finished second to [[Colombia national under-20 football team|Colombia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.d10.com.py/futbol/seleccion-paraguaya/26923-convocados-para-el-suda |title=Convocados para el Suda |publisher=D10 |date=2 January 2013 |language=es |access-date=8 September 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130104172616/http://www.d10.com.py/futbol/seleccion-paraguaya/26923-convocados-para-el-suda |archive-date=4 January 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.d10.com.py/futbol/seleccion-paraguaya/28038-paraguay-es-subcampeon |title=Paraguay es subcampeón |publisher=D10 |date=4 February 2013 |language=es |access-date=8 September 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130529132727/http://www.d10.com.py/futbol/seleccion-paraguaya/28038-paraguay-es-subcampeon |archive-date=29 May 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Later that year, he was called up for the [[2013 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in Turkey, where Paraguay reached the last 16.<ref>{{cite news |title=Sub 20: Convocados de Paraguay |url=http://espndeportes.espn.com/noticias/nota?s=fut&id=1816411&type=story |access-date=7 February 2019 |website=ESPN |date=1 June 2013 |language=es}}</ref>

On 5 September 2015, Almirón made his [[Paraguay national football team|senior international]] debut in a 3–2 friendly loss away to [[Chile national football team|Chile]], playing the final nine minutes in place of [[Jonathan Fabbro]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Chile con tanto de Alexis Sánchez venció 3–2 a Paraguay en Santiago |url=https://rpp.pe/futbol/mas-futbol/chile-con-tanto-de-alexis-sanchez-vencio-3-2-a-paraguay-en-santiago-noticia-833153 |access-date=19 February 2019 |publisher=RPP |date=5 September 2015 |language=es}}</ref> Manager [[Ramón Díaz]] called him up the following May for the [[Copa América Centenario]] in the United States, where he started two matches in a group-stage exit.<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Paraguay reveals Copa America Centenario final roster |url=https://www.si.com/planet-futbol/2016/05/09/paraguay-copa-america-centenario-roster |access-date=19 February 2019 |magazine=Sports Illustrated |date=9 May 2016}}</ref>

In March 2019, in a friendly against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] at [[Levi's Stadium]], Almirón came on as a substitute. Seven minutes later, he received a straight red card for a foul on [[José Juan Vázquez]] in which he dragged his studs down the back of the opponent's leg.<ref>{{cite news |last1=McCormick |first1=Sean |title=Newcastle United star Miguel Almiron sent off for Paraguay after horror challenge against Mexico |url=https://www.chroniclelive.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/newcastle-united-star-miguel-almiron-16032922 |access-date=1 April 2019 |work=Chronicle Live |date=27 March 2019}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Paraguay during the 4–2 victory against [[Jordan national football team|Jordan]] on 10 September 2019,<ref>{{Cite web |title=Jordan vs. Paraguay 2019‐09-10 |url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/matches/report/24004/Jordan_Paraguay.html |website=National Football Teams}}</ref> and on 10 October 2019, he was sent off for diving in a 1–0 friendly loss to [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Knight |first=Chris |title=Newcastle United forward Miguel Almiron sent off for Paraguay in friendly against Serbia |url=https://www.chroniclelive.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/miguel-almiron-paraguay-newcastle-united-17067677 |access-date=10 October 2019 |work=Chronicle Live |date=10 October 2019}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Almirón was born on 10 February 1994, in [[San Pablo (Asunción)|San Pablo]], a neighborhood of [[Asunción]], in a family environment marked by economic constraints.<ref name=v/> His father, Rubén Almirón, worked 18-hour shifts as a security guard, while his mother, Sonia Rejala, worked at a supermarket.<ref name=v>{{cite web |url=https://www.lanacion.com.py/futboledicion-impresa/2022/12/23/miggy-almiron-recuerda-a-sus-padres/ |title='Miggy' Almirón recuerda a sus padres |date=23 December 2022 |access-date=7 October 2023 |website=La Nación |language=es}}</ref> The house shared by the seven family members had only three bedrooms, which meant that Almirón had to share a bed with his mother until he was 18.<ref>{{cite web |last=Lennox |first=Joe |url=https://lifebogger.com/es/miguel-almiron-childhood-story-plus-datos-no-contados-de-la-biograf%C3%ADa/ |title=Historia de la infancia de Miguel Almiron más hechos no contados de la biografía |access-date=7 October 2023 |website=Life Bogger |language=es}}</ref> For much of his childhood, he lived with his grandparents.<ref name=v/> Almirón is [[Catholic]], as evidenced by two religious quotes tattooed on his arms.<ref name=ga>{{cite web |last=Taylor |first=Louise |date=11 November 2022 |title='Angel of the North': how Almirón found form to fire Newcastle dreams |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/nov/11/angel-of-the-north-how-almiron-found-form-to-fire-newcastle-dreams |website=[[The Guardian]] |access-date=12 November 2022}}</ref> He married his high school sweetheart, [[Alexia Notto]], who is a dancer, [[Zumba]] instructor, and [[influencer]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Kostadinova |first=Martina |url=https://ohmyfootball.com/es/news/866/almiron-wife-alexia-notto |title=¿Quién es la esposa de Miguel Almiron? Conoce a la impresionante Alexia Notto |date=24 October 2021 |website=Oh My Football |language=es}}</ref> The marriage took place on 29 August 2016,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lanacion.com.py/lnpop/2021/08/29/miguel-almiron-y-alexia-notto-celebran-su-quinto-aniversario-de-matrimonio/ |title=Miguel Almirón y Alexia Notto celebran su quinto aniversario de matrimonio |date=29 August 2021 |access-date=7 October 2023 |website=La Nación |language=es}}</ref> and on 6 June 2021, they welcomed their first child, Francesco.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lanacion.com.py/lnpop/2021/06/06/llego-francesco-el-primer-hijo-de-miguel-almiron-y-alexia-notto/ |title=Llegó Francesco, el primer hijo de Miguel Almirón y Alexia Notto |website=[[La Nación (Paraguay)|La Nación]] |date=6 June 2021 |access-date=15 November 2022 |language=es}}</ref>

